    "summary": "George Molenkamp was born in Australia, lived shortly in Batavia (Dutch East Indies)  and was educated in the Netherlands. \n\nAfter completion of his academic studies and PhD research in natural sciences and mathematics, he worked from 1974-1985 for the State Public Health Supervisory Body in The Hague. \n\nHe left the public service in 1985 and started within Touche Ross (an accountancy and advisory firm, now Deloitte) in The Hague a consulting business with a new vision: focussing on management of environmental issues in companies from a business and management perspective. \n\nHis group was the first in Europe setting the foundations for environmental and sustainability management and auditing in companies and corporate sustainability reporting and auditing. In 1988 he was appointed as partner.\n\nHe joined with his entire group KPMG in 1992 as a partner of KPMG. He was there the founder and chairman of KPMG Global Sustainability Services (now KPMG CC&S with 700 professionals in 50 countries) until his retirement  1 October 2007.\n\nHe has worked with companies in more than 35 countries and closely involved in work in the field of corporate responsibility for multinational corporations in Europe, South America, Australia and Asia (Japan, South Korea, China) in almost all the business sectors, and the Dutch and German government.\n\nHe has contributed to numerous publications in the international press and to business magazines, and has written handbooks for business and gave more than thousand presentations for conferences and seminars and interviews for the press in about 40 countries. \n\nIn 1995 he was named as  part-time Professor at the University of Amsterdam.After his retirement in October 2007 he became a member of the Sustainability Advisory Board of KPMG and is member of  other advisory boards across the business sector and at the University of Amsterdam.\n\nSpecialties: Strategy and Management of Sustainability and Corporate Responsibility",
